  <Summary>This issue contains two stories:

The History Holocaust Martian inventor Tallus blames John Carter for the changes in some of the customs on Barsoom and devises a plan to kill him. A trap is set and John Carter walks right into it falling into a deep sleep. While is this state of consciousness, John Carter dreams of several battles from earth's history.

Tales of Barsoom! A short account from Edgar Rice Burrough's The God's of Mars retells the early years of Barsoom when life first began.</Summary>
